title.value: TODODom: Domain Module for Task-Oriented Dialogue management Ontology (TODO)

comment.undefined: Element that leaves a record of a Skill obtained throughout the dialogue process.

comment.en: Information that is sent to the system to perform an execution or as argument for an execution, in a format that is understandable to the target system.
Grammar to be used by Foma to perform Key Element Extraction.

example.value:
Frame: Losing

FrameHead: lose (LexicalUnit: lose.v)

ArgumentSet:
* Owner [Core]
* Possession [Core]
* Place [Optional]
* Time [Optional]
...

For the sentence "My mother lost her watch at home":
"[My mother - owner(C)] LOST [her watch - possession(C)] (at home - place (O))"

comment.en: Word (or more than one) that evokes a specific situation or event, with its specific participants; that is, a frame. It is represented by one or more LexicalUnits.

example.value:
"baño" hasTSRI "coords_baño"
"baño" hasTSRI "ID_baño" 

"coords_baño" is of ParameterType "coordinate"
"ID_baño" is of ParameterType "ID"

comment.undefined: Establishes the type of parameter of a TSRI.
Element that leaves a record of an Argument obtained throughout the dialogue process.
Target System Readable Information corresponding to elements of the class WorldElement.
Element that covers the information to execute an Action that is executable through a command (vs. as a Service).
Target System Readable Information corresponding to elements of the class Action that require information in a Command format.
Target System Readable Information corresponding to elements of the class Action that point to Services.
Element that leaves a record of an Intent obtained throughout the dialogue process.

example.value:
User request: "I want information about Mona Lisa"

Intent: receive_information

comment.en: User intention when formulating a request.

comment.undefined: Target System Readable Information corresponding to elements of the class Argument.
Establishes the TSRI type of a given Action/Parameter.

example.value: (For a multipurpose robot) Guide, provide_information, pick, place

comment.undefined: Element that makes reference to the functionalities of the target system.

example.value:
Frame: Losing

ArgumentSet:
* Owner [Core]
* Possession [Core]
* Place [Optional]
* Time [Optional]
...

For the sentence "My mother lost her watch at home":
"[My mother - owner(C)] LOST [her watch - possession(C)] (at home - place (O))"

comment.undefined: Participant that is involved in the event described by the Frame. It can be Core (its presence is compulsory to convey the event) or Optional (its presence is not compulsory, but it adds additional information).
Agrupation of WorldElements of similar characteristics.
Target System Readable Information corresponding to elements of the class Action.
Element that makes reference to the capabilities of the target system.

example.value:
Frame: Losing

FrameHead: lose (LexicalUnit: lose.v)

ArgumentSet:

* Place [Optional]

comment.en: A specific event or situation evoked by a specific word (FrameHead), along with its participants (Arguments).

comment.undefined: Element that leaves a record of an Action obtained throughout the dialogue process.

example.value:
Action: obtain_information -> it is directed towards API REST service
The TSRI for obtain_information has an ActionType "service".
